surprised.

We started this company, after all, with the recognition that both sides of=
 the journalism marketplace had changed, and irreversibly so. Given the she=
er preponderance of content=E2=80=94a genetically modified word I=E2=80=99l=
l only ever speak as a second language=E2=80=94consumers had too many choic=
es, and the gruel was often too thin. Sophisticated readers increasingly wa=
nted to select their information intake with the same powers of curation th=
at guided other parts of their lives=E2=80=94and they wanted to read work t=
hat would improve them, professionally and cerebrally, and it didn=E2=80=99=
t hurt if they laughed from time to time. (It never does=E2=80=A6)

