inished product. To subscribe to their work meant to subscribe to them, and=
 have access to all their powers of wisdom and wit, the murmurs they were i=
mbibing, and the thoughts they were hypothesizing. As I=E2=80=99ve noted re=
lentlessly in this
column in the past, elite journalists are extraordinary amalgams of writers=
, storytellers, domain experts, conveners, and omniscient consultants. We=
